    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-09-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-09-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="152" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d152">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 2060.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-09-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 25,</hi> 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 13th of September,
                            No. 1447, has been received, and the proceeding on your part therein
                            mentioned is approved.</p>
                <p>It is somewhat remarkable, as a coincidence, that the impression
                            communicated to you by Lord Stanley is, in sentiment and to the letter,
                            the same which I announced to Sir Frederick Bruce, at Auburn, upon
                            reading the letter from Lord Stanley, the reply to which was contained
                            in my 2037.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
